title: Taner Öner
text:
Taner Öner (born March 4, 1971) is a Turkish <a href="association%20football">football</a> <a href="Coach%20%28sports%29%23Football">manager</a>. Currently, he serves as the manager of the <a href="Istanbul">Istanbul</a>-based <a href="Ata%C5%9Fehir%20Belediyespor">Ataşehir Belediyespor</a> in the <a href="Turkish%20Women%27s%20First%20Football%20League">Turkish Women's First Football League</a>.
Taner Öner was born in <a href="Erzincan">Erzincan</a>, Turkey on March 4, 1971.
His team <a href="Ata%C5%9Fehir%20Belediyespor">Ataşehir Belediyespor</a> finished the <a href="2016%E2%80%9317%20Turkish%20Women%27s%20First%20Football%20League">2016–17 Turkish Women's First League</a> season after the play-offs at third place. In the <a href="2017%E2%80%9318%20Turkish%20Women%27s%20First%20Football%20League">2017–18</a> season, he enjoyed league championship with his team.
